  "prompt": "What are the stats for WordPress, Drupal, and Joomla installs on the web?",
  "response": "As of the most recent data available (October 2023), WordPress, Drupal, and Joomla are three of the most popular content management systems (CMS) on the web. Here\u2019s an overview of their market share and usage statistics:\n\n---\n\n### **WordPress**\n- **Market Share**: WordPress dominates the CMS market, powering approximately **43% of all websites** and **65% of websites with a known CMS**.\n- **Websites**: Over **810 million websites** globally use WordPress.\n- **Usage Growth**: WordPress continues to grow, with millions of new installs yearly.\n- **Popularity**: It\u2019s the go-to CMS for bloggers, small businesses, and even large enterprises (e.g., The New York Times, Sony, and Disney use WordPress).\n- **Extensions**: Over **60,000 free plugins** and thousands of themes are available in the WordPress repository.\n\n---\n\n### **Drupal**\n- **Market Share**: Drupal holds about **1.5% of the CMS market** and powers around **0.8% of all websites**.\n- **Websites**: Approximately **1 million websites** use Drupal.\n- **Target Audience**: Drupal is popular among large organizations, governments, and enterprises due to its scalability and security.\n- **Notable Users**: The White House, NASA, and Tesla use Drupal.\n- **Extensions**: Drupal has over **50,000 modules** and thousands of themes available.\n\n---\n\n### **Joomla**\n- **Market Share**: Joomla has a **2.7% share of the CMS market** and powers around **1.4% of all websites**.\n- **Websites**: Roughly **1.8 million websites** use Joomla.\n- **Target Audience**: Joomla is often used for small to medium-sized businesses and community websites.\n- **Extensions**: Joomla has over **8,000 extensions** available in its directory.\n\n---\n\n### **Comparison Overview**\n| **CMS**      | **Market Share (CMS)** | **Total Websites** | **Strengths**                     |\n|--------------|------------------------|--------------------|-----------------------------------|\n| **WordPress**| 65%                   | ~810 million       | Ease of use, vast ecosystem       |\n| **Drupal**   | 1.5%                  | ~1 million         | Scalability, security            |\n| **Joomla**   | 2.7%                  | ~1.8 million       | Flexibility, community support   |\n\n---\n\n### **Trends**\n- WordPress continues to dominate due to its user-friendly interface, extensive plugin library, and strong community support.\n- Drupal remains a favorite for enterprise-level websites requiring high security and scalability.\n- Joomla has seen a decline in market share but remains a solid choice for specific use cases.\n\nThese statistics highlight WordPress\u2019s dominance, while Drupal and Joomla cater to niche markets with specific needs.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
